spec: socket_extra172
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(socket)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/socket.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/socket.html — Python socket module documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/socket.py"
    - "CPython source: Modules/socketmodule.c"
    - "socket_extra171.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.__name__/__package__/__spec__/__loader__ module-level identity and socket.socket.__dict__ accept/close/detach/fileno membership (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra170.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.AF_UNIX/__SOCK_RAW enum constants and SOL_SOCKET/__SO_REUSEADDR plain int constants (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra169.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.socket.__dict__ connect/makefile/sendfile membership and __dict__.__len__()==28 (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra167.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.AddressFamily/__SocketKind __name__/__module__/__bases__[0].__name__=='IntEnum' and name lengths (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra165.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.error/__timeout/__gaierror/__herror class identity (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra159.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.socket.__name__/__module__/__bases__[0].__name__ (table + invariants)."
    - "socket.zspec / early extras — cover socket.__name__=='socket' and socket.__package__ (base spec)."
  notes:
    - "This spec does NOT duplicate invariants present in socket_extra93 through socket_extra171."
    - "Wave 354 theme: socket.socket.__mro__ length / socket.AddressFamily.__mro__ length / socket.SocketKind.__mro__ length / socket.gaierror.__mro__ length / socket.herror.__mro__ length. socket_extra167 anchors AddressFamily/__SocketKind bases; socket_extra165 anchors gaierror/herror class identity. This spec anchors all five MRO chain lengths as primary novel content."
    - "socket.socket.__mro__.__len__() == 3. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0. MRO: (socket.socket, _socket.socket, object) — 3 classes."
    - "socket.AddressFamily.__mro__.__len__() == 6. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0. MRO: (AddressFamily, IntEnum, int, ReprEnum, Enum, object) — 6 classes."
    - "socket.SocketKind.__mro__.__len__() == 6. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0. MRO: (SocketKind, IntEnum, int, ReprEnum, Enum, object) — 6 classes."
    - "socket.gaierror.__mro__.__len__() == 5. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0. MRO: (gaierror, OSError, Exception, BaseException, object) — 5 classes."
    - "socket.herror.__mro__.__len__() == 5. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0. MRO: (herror, OSError, Exception, BaseException, object) — 5 classes."
    - "Note: socket.socket.__mro__ == (socket.socket, _socket.socket, object). socket.socket is a Python subclass of _socket.socket (the C extension base); the MRO has 3 elements because there is one C intermediate class. socket.socket.__mro__.__len__()==3 is 1 more than the minimum (2) and much less than the enum MRO lengths (6)."
    - "Note: socket.AddressFamily.__mro__ == (AddressFamily, IntEnum, int, ReprEnum, Enum, object). The IntEnum MRO is 6 classes deep because IntEnum inherits from int, ReprEnum, and Enum, each adding to the chain. AddressFamily.__mro__.__len__()==6 == SocketKind.__mro__.__len__()==6."
    - "Note: socket.gaierror.__mro__ == (gaierror, OSError, Exception, BaseException, object). gaierror inherits from OSError which adds one extra class compared to plain Exception subclasses (which have 4-class MROs). gaierror.__mro__.__len__()==5 == herror.__mro__.__len__()==5."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
  created_at: "2026-04-11T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

